<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Europe. Known by a few records from the European part of Russia, Ukraine and Slovakia (
<bibRefCitation author="Humala, A. E." journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Karelian Research Centre of the Russian Academy of Sciences. Biogeography Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="53 - 75" title="On the insect fauna of south-east Karelia" volume="9" year="2009">Humala and Polevoi 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jakovlev, E. B." editor="Kravchenko, A. V." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre RAS, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="Flora and Fauna of the Nature Protected Territories of Karelia" year="1997">Jakovlev and Polevoi 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Martinovsky, J" journalOrPublisher="Casopis Slezskeho Zemskeho Muzea ser. A - Vedy Prirodni" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="73 - 78" title="First records of Synneuronannulipes Lundstroem (Synneuridae) and Mesaxymyiakerteszi (Duda) (Axymyiidae) from Slovakia, with notes on their taxonomy and biology (Diptera)" volume="42" year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martinovský">Martinovsky</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Roháček">Rohacek</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Poorly known. Larvae were collected from spruce wood (
<bibRefCitation author="Mamaev, B" journalOrPublisher="Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="168 - 180" title="New data on the taxonomy and biology of Diptera of the family Axymyiidae" volume="45" year="1966">Mamaev and Krivosheina 1966</bibRefCitation>
) and adults found sitting on very damp fir logs (
<bibRefCitation author="Martinovsky, J" journalOrPublisher="Casopis Slezskeho Zemskeho Muzea ser. A - Vedy Prirodni" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="73 - 78" title="First records of Synneuronannulipes Lundstroem (Synneuridae) and Mesaxymyiakerteszi (Duda) (Axymyiidae) from Slovakia, with notes on their taxonomy and biology (Diptera)" volume="42" year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martinovský">Martinovsky</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Roháček">Rohacek</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Krivosheina, N P" editor="Baranchikov, Y N" journalOrPublisher="U. S. Department of Agriculture, Forest Service, Northeastern Forest Experiment Station, Randor" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="Forest Insect Guilds: Patterns of Interaction with Host Tree" year="1991">Krivosheina (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, larvae of 
<taxonomicName family="Axymyiidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" rank="family">Axymyiidae</taxonomicName>
may colonise newly fallen trunks and stay there for several years. This species was collected from a wind-broken aspen, colonised by 7 species of macrofungi Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
